                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5mFR62",
                    "body": "I think it will be slightly more convenient to use `(2 : R)`. I also prefer not to place new lines in a term (the equalty in this case) unless necessary. Thus I suggest:\r\n```suggestion\r\nlemma reflection_reflection_iterate\r\n    (hfx : f x = 2) (hgy : g y = 2) (hgxfy : f y * g x = 4) (n : ℕ) :\r\n    ((reflection hgy).trans (reflection hfx))^[n] y = y + n • (f y • x - (2 : R) • y) := by\r\n```",
                    "createdAt": "2024-08-10T15:05:26Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "ocfnash"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5mFR7a",
                    "body": "I think this fixes the proof for the tweaked statement:\r\n```suggestion\r\n    simp only [iterate_succ', comp_apply, ih, two_smul, smul_sub, smul_add, map_add,\r\n      LinearEquiv.trans_apply, reflection_apply_self, map_neg, reflection_apply, neg_sub, map_sub,\r\n      map_nsmul, map_smul, smul_neg, hz, add_smul]\r\n```",
                    "createdAt": "2024-08-10T15:05:55Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "ocfnash"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5mFR_z",
                    "body": "I think there is a tiny result worth factoring out here. To be precise I suggest putting these lemmas at the bottom of `Mathlib.Algebra.Module.Torsion`:\r\n```lean\r\n@[simp]\r\nlemma infinite_range_add_smul_iff\r\n    [AddCommGroup M] [Ring R] [Module R M] [Infinite R] [NoZeroSMulDivisors R M] (x y : M) :\r\n    (Set.range <| fun r : R ↦ x + r • y).Infinite ↔ y ≠ 0 := by\r\n  refine ⟨fun h hy ↦ by simp [hy] at h, fun h ↦ Set.infinite_range_of_injective fun r s hrs ↦ ?_⟩\r\n  rw [add_right_inj] at hrs\r\n  exact smul_left_injective _ h hrs\r\n\r\n@[simp]\r\nlemma infinite_range_add_nsmul_iff\r\n    [AddCommGroup M] [NoZeroSMulDivisors ℤ M] (x y : M) :\r\n    (Set.range <| fun n : ℕ ↦ x + n • y).Infinite ↔ y ≠ 0 := by\r\n  refine ⟨fun h hy ↦ by simp [hy] at h, fun h ↦ Set.infinite_range_of_injective fun r s hrs ↦ ?_⟩\r\n  rw [add_right_inj, ← natCast_zsmul, ← natCast_zsmul] at hrs\r\n  simpa using smul_left_injective _ h hrs\r\n```\r\nso that we can shorten the proof here (and also upgrade it to an iff) as follows:\r\n```suggestion\r\nlemma infinite_range_reflection_reflection_iterate_iff [NoZeroSMulDivisors ℤ M]\r\n    (hfx : f x = 2) (hgy : g y = 2) (hgxfy : f y * g x = 4) :\r\n    (range <| fun n ↦ ((reflection hgy).trans (reflection hfx))^[n] y).Infinite ↔\r\n    f y • x ≠ (2 : R) • y := by\r\n  simp only [reflection_reflection_iterate hfx hgy hgxfy, infinite_range_add_nsmul_iff, sub_ne_zero]\r\n```\r\nI was 50-50 on whether we should state these results or their contrapositive but given your ultimate application I was persuaded this was the most convenient.",
                    "createdAt": "2024-08-10T15:08:30Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "ocfnash"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5mFSCM",
                    "body": "Again I suggest sticking to `(2 : R)` here:\r\n```suggestion\r\n  suffices h : f y • x = (2 : R) • y by\r\n    rw [hfy, two_smul R x, two_smul R y, ← two_zsmul, ← two_zsmul] at h\r\n    exact smul_right_injective _ two_ne_zero h\r\n```",
                    "createdAt": "2024-08-10T15:09:55Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "ocfnash"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5mFSDX",
                    "body": "And then given the changes above this becomes:\r\n```suggestion\r\napply ((infinite_range_reflection_reflection_iterate_iff hfx hgy\r\n    (by rw [hfy, hgx]; norm_cast)).mpr hΦ).mono\r\n```",
                    "createdAt": "2024-08-10T15:10:22Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "ocfnash"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5mFSE9",
                    "body": "Some small change will be necessary here too which I will leave to you (assuming you agree to the suggestions above).",
                    "createdAt": "2024-08-10T15:10:53Z",
